WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:14.960
Good evening, family.

00:00:14.960 --> 00:01:00.280
Thank you for joining us again today.

00:01:13.616 --> 00:01:29.784
I have an urgency to pray tonight, so I am not going to talk a lot.

00:01:29.784 --> 00:01:42.630
We are going to pray.

00:01:42.640 --> 00:01:56.838
We are just going to jump right in the river.

00:02:07.254 --> 00:02:28.108
I thought I would come prepared instead of having to cultivate it and then jump in the river.

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:54.096
I have been doing it all day long for what he has had me on assignment for.

00:02:54.096 --> 00:04:03.190
Something major is about to happen, and as I stepped over in the spirit when I was listening to these songs, I have just been in that place of prayer all day.

00:04:05.658 --> 00:04:58.165
I have been in that place with Diana and having him go through and, like I said, I feel like I am being examined right now.

00:04:58.650 --> 00:05:07.080
You know, whenever you have his gaze—is what I want to call it—he is examining you.

00:05:07.080 --> 00:05:10.270
He is looking over you with that magnifying glass.

00:05:30.195 --> 00:05:37.147
I told her, I said, 'I feel like I am being stripped as you are asking him to go to the next level, as you are asking him to go to this next place.

00:05:37.147 --> 00:07:32.310
' She has been reading this book to me and going over all these things of the bait of Satan.

00:07:32.320 --> 00:07:34.051
This book is just beautiful and it is exciting.

00:08:34.933 --> 00:08:35.613
A lot of correction, a lot of going from glory to glory, changing you and making sure that you are examining yourself underneath that potter's wheel with him, saying, 'God, am I where I need to be?

00:08:35.613 --> 00:08:39.740
' I felt like we should just jump right in it.

00:08:39.740 --> 00:08:44.790
Don't worry about it.

00:08:44.790 --> 00:08:45.440
Okay.

00:09:05.540 --> 00:09:05.760
That is awesome.

00:09:05.760 --> 00:09:06.200
Sorry.

00:09:13.360 --> 00:09:13.585
I saw you eyeing me sometimes like, 'What?

00:09:13.585 --> 00:09:16.227
' I was like, 'What am I doing?

00:09:16.227 --> 00:09:20.525
' No, thanks, appreciate it.

00:09:26.320 --> 00:09:26.505
I was like, 'What am I doing?

00:09:26.505 --> 00:09:27.618
Is it my vitamins?

00:09:27.618 --> 00:09:30.356
' Well, no, it is fine.

00:09:30.356 --> 00:09:33.800
We do not have to do any of that right now.

00:09:47.560 --> 00:09:47.940
You were just making me nervous because you were eyeing my face and I was thinking, 'What did I do?

00:09:47.940 --> 00:09:49.460
What is wrong?

00:09:49.460 --> 00:09:53.453
' I like, 'You want to talk here?

00:09:53.453 --> 00:09:57.503
Take it, because you are making me nervous.

00:09:57.503 --> 00:10:04.147
' I know when you are staring at me, I am thinking, 'What is going on?

00:10:04.147 --> 00:10:06.664
' We are just real, y'all.

00:10:13.380 --> 00:10:13.570
But she is feeling better, you know.

00:10:13.570 --> 00:10:13.996
Yes.

00:10:13.996 --> 00:10:14.702
Thank you.

00:10:14.702 --> 00:10:15.644
Stupid COVID virus.

00:10:15.644 --> 00:10:18.840
Thank you all for your prayers.

00:10:18.840 --> 00:10:23.350
She says, 'I can taste things today.

00:10:23.350 --> 00:10:26.270
' Yes, I am so thankful.

00:10:26.270 --> 00:10:31.144
Thank you guys for praying for me.

00:10:31.144 --> 00:10:37.858
Eating lettuce without dressing, she goes, 'I don't even know why I'm eating.

00:10:37.858 --> 00:10:41.720
' She goes, 'If you can't taste dressing, why do you even eat it?

00:10:41.720 --> 00:10:45.053
' I started eating salads without any dressing on it.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:47.800
I couldn't taste because it has been about six days.

00:10:48.378 --> 00:10:49.533
It is just habits.

00:10:49.533 --> 00:10:51.900
Like, why am I doing this?

00:10:51.900 --> 00:10:53.320
I can't taste it.

00:11:09.960 --> 00:11:10.257
She cannot even taste it anyway.

00:11:12.790 --> 00:11:13.915
So why am I wasting calories on it?

00:11:13.915 --> 00:11:19.360
You know, going there, and that is where we are, too.

00:11:19.537 --> 00:11:22.171
I have been working hard on my eating right.

00:11:22.171 --> 00:11:34.560
One of the things the Lord has been talking to me about, like I said, is examining myself and examining our family and our eating habits and things that we are going over.

00:11:34.880 --> 00:11:45.485
I really started out the year thinking, 'Well, we are going to lose weight, we are going to exercise, and we are going to do all this stuff.

00:11:45.485 --> 00:11:56.669
' Then you let one month go by and then another one goes by, and here we are going on into the third month of the year this week.

00:11:58.280 --> 00:12:00.455
The Lord spoke to me in my dream again and I said, 'Okay.

00:12:00.455 --> 00:12:03.069
' So over the last four days, he got onto me.

00:12:03.069 --> 00:12:07.827
He said, 'How do you know where you are, Brandon, if you do not weigh every day?

00:12:07.827 --> 00:12:09.640
You must weigh every day.

00:12:25.490 --> 00:12:25.680
You must take account of everything you are putting in your mouth.

00:12:25.680 --> 00:12:30.032
Watch your calories, watch the things that you are doing.

00:12:30.032 --> 00:12:36.280
' It is not just, 'Well, you know, I am trying to eat right.

00:12:36.280 --> 00:12:42.126
' He said, 'You are eating right, but you are eating too much of eating right.

00:12:42.126 --> 00:12:49.307
' Watch and monitor the calories of what he restricted me to in a diet and logging it.

00:12:52.760 --> 00:12:58.440
Be intentional about your eating, so that you live this way.

00:13:00.160 --> 00:13:08.192
I thought about doing a weight loss challenge with everybody, because there are so many of the body of Christ that are overcoming this.

00:13:08.192 --> 00:13:14.205
Especially in the Pentecostal realm, the charismatics have a lot of weight issues.

00:13:14.205 --> 00:13:16.320
I have noticed.

00:13:19.018 --> 00:13:28.720
To be that fit body, to be that body that is ready for these end times, is going to be a body that is bridled.

00:13:28.991 --> 00:13:35.200
How can you be bridled if you are not bridled in your eating?

00:13:43.696 --> 00:14:01.760
That is why he was really like, I came on, you know, even with what I told you all about pressure and rejection and overcoming that bully mentality of what I went through as a kid, finding comfort in food, and going to the store and finding things that are organic.

00:14:02.080 --> 00:14:07.640
I am going to find this and it is organic, it is going to be okay.

00:14:20.529 --> 00:14:21.524
I will eat this ice cream or I will eat that because it is organic.

00:14:26.053 --> 00:14:26.267
And I don't know, it is just she is just teaching me.

00:14:26.267 --> 00:14:31.440
Going through the store today, I met one of our watchers, our Instagram watchers.

00:14:31.440 --> 00:14:35.090
Do I have stuff on my face still?

00:14:35.090 --> 00:14:35.660
No.

00:14:35.660 --> 00:14:36.230
Okay.

00:14:36.230 --> 00:14:37.005
Making sure.

00:14:37.005 --> 00:14:38.235
Well, I love you.

00:14:46.093 --> 00:14:46.249
You have any right to say something.

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:54.000
But meeting somebody today in the grocery store and saying, 'Hey, I watch you on Instagram.

00:14:54.000 --> 00:15:03.480
' I thought, 'Wow, I forget that I am on Instagram,' because Braden is the one that does all that.

00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:10.589
I do not pay attention to all that social media stuff, but he is awesome.

00:15:26.850 --> 00:15:27.060
He uploads all that every day, all day doing that in the school.

00:15:30.720 --> 00:15:31.200
He is like, 'Dad, I put that out for you.

00:15:31.200 --> 00:15:36.800
' She was like, 'I watch you on Instagram.

00:15:36.800 --> 00:15:39.338
' I thought, 'Isn't that interesting?

00:15:40.013 --> 00:15:41.000
You don't watch us on YouTube.

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:43.903
You watch us on Instagram.

00:15:43.903 --> 00:15:46.089
' Just going over things, y'all.

00:15:48.338 --> 00:15:58.107
I think it is just time to get real with stuff and really search ourselves out for what the Lord said about 1 Corinthians 5:5 this year.

00:15:58.107 --> 00:16:03.440
He said, 'I will hide you in the cliff, Brandon, for what is coming.

00:16:07.907 --> 00:16:08.173
I am going to shake the church.

00:16:15.800 --> 00:16:18.360
I am going to shake the nations, and it will be on the just and the unjust.

00:16:18.360 --> 00:16:34.046
There is going to be a major shaking to awaken in all these areas.

00:16:34.046 --> 00:16:40.512
' He said, 'I will hide my remnant in the cliff of the rock.

00:16:40.512 --> 00:16:52.775
' I saw that shaking, because if you are already awake and you are already dealing with stuff, he is not going to have to shake you to awake you.

00:17:15.920 --> 00:17:16.360
You are already awake.

00:17:16.360 --> 00:17:29.680
But I saw the body of Christ; there was a remnant of us in the cliff of this rock.

00:17:41.440 --> 00:17:41.867
I saw this hatch over it and the glory was over it.

00:17:41.867 --> 00:17:52.795
I just want to stay in that, like what Kathryn Kuhlman always says, 'Let me be the apple of his eye.

00:17:52.795 --> 00:17:56.910
' Where is that scripture about the apple of his eye, love?

00:17:56.910 --> 00:17:59.545
She talks about it all the time.

00:18:08.800 --> 00:18:09.180
I know it is in Psalms.

00:18:09.180 --> 00:18:11.960
David said it, I believe.

00:18:11.960 --> 00:18:17.000
But just asking him to search me and know me.

00:18:17.000 --> 00:18:37.750
I expect over the next 6 months that I am going to be 60 pounds lighter and I am going to go back to where I was whenever the Lord challenged me the first time in my sleep.

00:18:37.750 --> 00:18:43.227
Psalm 17:8, David prays, 'Keep me as the apple of the eye.

00:18:43.227 --> 00:18:46.700
Hide me under the shadow of thy wings.

00:18:46.700 --> 00:18:48.060
' Psalms what?

00:18:48.060 --> 00:18:48.740
17:8.

00:18:48.740 --> 00:18:51.418
Keep me as the apple of eye.

00:18:51.636 --> 00:18:52.289
I want that.

00:18:58.147 --> 00:19:00.235
That your gaze is always upon me, that you are always looking towards me, that you are examining me.

00:19:09.693 --> 00:19:11.876
Even whenever there is something that you do not like, change it.

00:19:11.876 --> 00:19:22.550
Create in me that clean heart that whenever I stand before you, I am that vessel that has been purified by fire.

00:19:22.550 --> 00:19:23.550
Purify my heart.

00:19:23.550 --> 00:19:24.970
Let me be as gold.

00:19:33.320 --> 00:19:33.500
That ladle of his hand scooping the impurities out of your life, even whenever they are rising to the surface and you feel so vulnerable.

00:19:33.500 --> 00:19:35.580
That is what I have told her.

00:19:39.451 --> 00:19:50.540
I feel you feel so vulnerable lately when his gaze is upon you, when he is cleaning you up, and you are getting that self out of the way, and you are going, What hides?

00:19:50.540 --> 00:19:53.333
Well, your walk is an issue.

00:19:53.333 --> 00:20:02.549
Okay, what else can I do to exercise, take care of yourself, there are other things.

00:20:02.549 --> 00:20:03.783
Look at this.

00:20:06.617 --> 00:20:31.480
As you deal with that stuff, and when John read that little bit about what he said about leadership and about the fatherless, what I have always gone about the fatherless, the body of Christ that does not have a dad, there are a lot of fatherless children out there that need this.

00:20:31.480 --> 00:20:38.211
I felt like a lot of times, this part of this chapter spoke so loud to me.

00:20:38.211 --> 00:20:48.560
So I thought if it spoke so loud to me, maybe it would help you because there are certain things that she said today.

00:20:48.560 --> 00:20:52.954
Go ahead and just read some of that.

00:20:57.192 --> 00:20:57.608
It is really good.

00:21:06.800 --> 00:21:07.103
I have seen this cry.

00:21:07.103 --> 00:21:10.017
So, it says, Where are the fathers?

00:21:10.017 --> 00:21:15.424
I have seen this cry in countless men and women in the body of Christ.

00:21:15.424 --> 00:21:22.057
Most of them are young and with a strong call of God on their lives.

00:21:22.057 --> 00:21:28.267
They cry out for a father, a man to disciple, love, support, and encourage them.

00:21:28.267 --> 00:21:44.747
This is why God said that he would turn the hearts of the fathers, the leaders to the children, the people, and the hearts of the children to their fathers, lest I come and strike the earth with a curse.

00:21:44.747 --> 00:21:45.613
Malachi 4:6.

00:21:45.613 --> 00:21:55.535
Our nation lost its fathers, dads, leaders, or ministers in the 1940s and 1950s, and today our condition is getting worse.

00:21:55.535 --> 00:22:04.858
Not unlike Saul, many leaders in our homes, corporations, and churches are more concerned with their goals than with their offspring.

00:22:04.858 --> 00:22:16.480
Because of this attitude, these leaders view God's people as resources to serve their vision instead of seeing the vision as the vehicle to serve the people.

00:22:25.954 --> 00:22:26.371
The success of the vision justifies the cost of wounded lives and shattered people.

00:22:26.371 --> 00:22:33.011
Justice, mercy, integrity, and love are compromised for success.

00:22:33.011 --> 00:22:37.453
Decisions are based on money, numbers, and results.

00:22:50.853 --> 00:22:51.667
This opens the door to treatment such as David received.

00:22:51.667 --> 00:22:57.182
After all, Saul had a kingdom to protect.

00:22:57.182 --> 00:23:06.200
This type of treatment is acceptable in the leaders' minds because they are pursuing the furtherance of the gospel.

00:23:06.200 --> 00:23:11.430
How many leaders have cut off men under them because of suspicion?

00:23:11.430 --> 00:23:13.343
Why are those leaders suspicious?

00:23:13.343 --> 00:23:16.125
Because they are not serving God.

00:23:33.514 --> 00:23:33.709
They are serving a vision.

00:23:33.709 --> 00:23:40.702
Like Saul, they are insecure in their calling and that breeds jealousy and pride.

00:23:57.387 --> 00:23:57.913
They recognize qualities in people that they know are godly and they are willing to use those people as long as it benefits them.

00:23:57.913 --> 00:24:05.647
Saul enjoyed the success of David until he saw it as a threat to him.

00:24:05.647 --> 00:24:13.125
Then he demoted David and watched for a reason to destroy him.

00:24:22.497 --> 00:24:22.651
I have talked through with countless young men and women who cried out for accountability.

00:24:23.450 --> 00:24:25.640
They wanted to be submitted to a leader who would disciple them.

00:24:27.829 --> 00:24:28.286
They felt isolated and alone.

00:24:28.286 --> 00:24:31.909
They were seeking someone to father them.

00:24:37.960 --> 00:24:38.280
But God allowed them to go through rejection because God wanted to do in them what he had done in David.

00:24:38.280 --> 00:24:42.513
Listen carefully to what the Spirit is saying.

00:24:42.513 --> 00:24:49.185
David was concerned that Saul believed he was rebellious and evil.

00:24:49.185 --> 00:24:53.796
David must have searched his heart saying, Where have I gone wrong?

00:24:58.680 --> 00:24:59.000
How was Saul's heart turned against me so quickly?

00:24:59.000 --> 00:25:09.360
That is why he cried out, Someone urged me to kill you, but I said no.

00:25:21.375 --> 00:25:22.600
I only cut off the corner of your robe so that you could know and see that there is neither evil nor rebellion in my hand.

00:25:22.600 --> 00:25:24.430
See 1st Samuel 24.

00:25:24.430 --> 00:25:33.360
David thought if he could prove his love for Saul, Saul would restore him to favor and the prophecy would be fulfilled.

00:25:43.977 --> 00:25:44.400
People who have been rejected by a father or leader tend to take all the blame on themselves.

00:25:44.400 --> 00:25:48.593
They are imprisoned by tormenting thoughts of, What did I do?

00:25:54.720 --> 00:25:54.964
and, Was my heart impure?

00:25:59.660 --> 00:25:59.795
They sometimes wonder who turned the heart of my leader against me.

00:25:59.795 --> 00:26:03.698
Then they constantly try to prove their innocence to their leaders.

00:26:14.371 --> 00:26:14.680
They think that if they can only show their loyalty and value, they will be accepted.

00:26:14.680 --> 00:26:18.440
Sadly, the more they try, the more rejected they feel.

00:26:28.320 --> 00:26:28.687
So, I have dealt with this a lot.

00:26:31.103 --> 00:26:32.720
That paragraph right there is a summary of my life.

00:26:37.960 --> 00:26:46.175
I felt like when she read that to me, I was just going over this book, and it has helped me so much—the bait of Satan, and walking in offense towards leadership.

00:26:46.175 --> 00:26:53.293
Who I always talk about, you know, when I say, Where are the fathers?

00:26:53.293 --> 00:26:56.920
Where are the fathers of the faith?

00:26:56.920 --> 00:27:07.594
There is so much rejection, and in our case, the Lord has blessed us so much with so many people following us so quickly.

00:27:07.594 --> 00:27:13.655
It seems to be, the bigger it gets, the more rejection you receive from people.

00:27:13.655 --> 00:27:15.560
She brought up some other ministries.

00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:17.120
She said, Brandon, isn't it amazing?

00:27:17.120 --> 00:27:22.102
Have you ever seen so and so do a conference?

00:27:22.102 --> 00:27:25.560
They are always alone.

00:27:25.560 --> 00:27:26.314
Why?

00:27:26.314 --> 00:27:31.526
Because they have some of the biggest churches in Oklahoma.

00:27:31.526 --> 00:27:34.760
He has the biggest church in Oklahoma.

00:27:34.760 --> 00:27:39.697
He has plants around the whole world and he does not hang around this.

00:27:41.120 --> 00:27:47.040
And then she went over, do you know this pastor?

00:27:49.222 --> 00:27:52.320
And so we went over and I said, Isn't that interesting?

00:27:52.320 --> 00:28:02.280
They are criticized more than they are about what they are not doing or how they are not preaching right or whatever.

00:28:12.320 --> 00:28:12.600
And there is so much criticism towards it, but it comes out of a jealousy and an envy.

00:28:12.600 --> 00:28:15.440
People compare because they feel less than.

00:28:35.914 --> 00:28:36.263
And so I have realized as watching this, that is why some of these—because I always said, Why do they?

00:28:36.263 --> 00:28:44.805
When she brought that up today, she was talking to me about it.

00:28:44.805 --> 00:28:46.543
I said, Why do they do that?

00:28:48.293 --> 00:28:48.587
That is interesting, love.

00:28:48.587 --> 00:28:55.440
And we started going over it, and the Holy Spirit was ministering to me all day long.

00:29:13.103 --> 00:29:13.451
And then he was dealing with me with this kind of stuff.

00:29:13.451 --> 00:29:21.560
But we were praying for what is about to happen with Iran and the attacks on our soil, the storm that I feel is about to happen, that we are right at it.

00:29:22.400 --> 00:29:30.180
And when I went into the spirit, I have been very watchful over how I release things when I am seeing it even live.

00:29:35.691 --> 00:29:38.840
I hold things back a lot because of not feeling a release necessarily, because people cannot handle it, because you have such a variety of mature believers and immature believers.

00:29:39.850 --> 00:29:44.267
And so it is interesting because that is why I try to say, and maybe I come across harsh saying, there is 99.

00:29:44.267 --> 00:29:47.920
9% of you that have no idea how to have a relationship with him.

00:29:47.920 --> 00:29:52.455
And the ones that are mature, because the mature believers go, Well, that is offensive.

00:30:00.720 --> 00:30:00.940
And they are doing exactly what I am talking about.

00:30:00.940 --> 00:30:01.820
Don't be offended.

00:30:09.253 --> 00:30:09.947
I am not trying to pick at you.

00:30:09.947 --> 00:30:27.533
I am saying I have a lot of people that do not have a clue anything about the spirit realm and you are trying to educate because there are no fathers teaching it at church.

00:30:27.533 --> 00:30:32.427
There is not a lot of spiritual backbone at church anymore.

00:30:37.760 --> 00:30:42.440
And I have noticed when I have a survey and I ask people, Where do you go to church?

00:30:42.440 --> 00:30:44.640
We do not go to church.

00:30:44.640 --> 00:30:45.897
We watch online.

00:30:45.897 --> 00:30:47.120
We are offended.

00:30:47.120 --> 00:30:49.714
We don't want to go to church.

00:30:50.137 --> 00:30:52.320
And I come across more like to the lady today.

00:30:52.320 --> 00:30:55.965
She went to church, a local church in Tulsa.

00:31:01.920 --> 00:31:02.140
And it is very seldom that I come across somebody that says, Well, I go to church.

00:31:08.263 --> 00:31:08.674
So, well, we do not go to church.

00:31:08.674 --> 00:31:09.909
Well, why?

00:31:09.909 --> 00:31:11.547
Well, because we were offended.

00:31:17.160 --> 00:31:22.200
And that is why I wanted to bring this to the body of Christ even more after the Lord dealt with me about it.

00:31:22.200 --> 00:31:23.617
There are so many fatherless children.

00:31:23.617 --> 00:31:30.745
There are so many people that are not in church anymore because they do not want to go to church.

00:31:51.309 --> 00:31:51.606
They are offended at the pastor.

00:31:56.960 --> 00:31:57.240
They're offended at the Christian.

00:32:02.846 --> 00:32:03.040
You know, brother, I don't need church anymore.

00:32:04.768 --> 00:32:05.272
I find it online.

00:32:06.587 --> 00:32:06.893
I teach.

00:32:14.480 --> 00:32:14.849
And I was one of those for 10 years.

00:32:14.849 --> 00:32:35.890
Diana and I wouldn't go anywhere because of Megan, and we said, Well, the last time the usher told us to get up and leave because she was disrupting service, I vowed I'd never step foot back in another church again until she was better.

00:32:35.890 --> 00:32:47.909
Because it was so humiliating already to come because we couldn't put her in children's church because of how bad she was when she was really overcoming.

00:32:47.909 --> 00:32:52.120
And when the usher asked us, say, She's a disruption in the service, sir.

00:32:52.120 --> 00:32:53.267
Can you please leave?

00:33:01.080 --> 00:33:01.400
And I vowed at that time, I told her, I said, I will never go back to church, and we didn't for 10 years.

00:33:04.907 --> 00:33:05.133
We watched online only.

00:33:05.133 --> 00:33:07.227
And I'm just being really transparent.

00:33:07.227 --> 00:33:09.160
I'm just being real.

00:33:24.954 --> 00:33:25.257
And I said, You know what?

00:33:25.257 --> 00:33:27.417
Church isn't for us.

00:33:27.417 --> 00:33:29.728
We'll just watch TV.

00:33:48.080 --> 00:33:48.411
And I got so bitter and so offended in my heart about everybody in the body of Christ.

00:33:50.069 --> 00:33:56.529
And I let that wall of offense build a mountain until the Holy Spirit started stripping it down and I realized I was wrong.

00:33:56.529 --> 00:34:03.720
And yeah, that usher was rude, but he was just a cranky old man.

00:34:11.733 --> 00:34:11.884
I forgive him.

00:34:14.200 --> 00:34:14.351
And you move on.

00:34:17.800 --> 00:34:18.573
But I know there's a lot of you that walk in that offense.

00:34:18.573 --> 00:34:21.853
Well, you know, I was dealt this way.

00:34:26.380 --> 00:34:26.640
I was dealt that way.

00:34:26.640 --> 00:34:26.899
Why?

00:34:31.720 --> 00:34:35.700
Because I come across you all the time and people tell me I only watch online.

00:34:53.000 --> 00:34:53.200
I don't we are the church, brother.

00:34:53.200 --> 00:34:57.396
We don't need to go to church.

00:35:02.175 --> 00:35:06.976
But as I have read what Jesus said in Matthew 24 that many will be offended in these last days, there will be many false prophets.

00:35:25.440 --> 00:35:30.372
And you start to put it together that the ones that are not being shepherded, the ones that are off in la-la land over here by themselves out of offense, that spirit of offense, that root of offense is what makes it where you don't have discerning.

00:35:37.650 --> 00:35:38.976
You're not hearing him because if you can't forgive your brother of his trespasses, the Father said he won't forgive you of yours.

00:35:41.366 --> 00:35:49.971
So, you've allowed that offense and that root of bitterness to come in your heart so much that I don't want to hear anybody at church.

00:35:49.971 --> 00:35:55.640
I'm not going to go around the flock anymore.

00:36:05.311 --> 00:36:05.493
And we did it.

00:36:05.493 --> 00:36:06.290
I'm telling you.

00:36:10.460 --> 00:36:17.920
And it took a breaking down, and I started going, and we went to Billy Burke meetings, and that's when we started getting free.

00:36:27.120 --> 00:36:35.805
And I'm telling you, after you go to these things and you get a touch from the Father and you get a drink, you go, Man, I could just go and be a part of congregation.

00:36:42.080 --> 00:36:48.227
And I'm telling you, Glorious and these some other places, I don't like to mention it because I don't want everybody saying, Hey, we're going to move there.

00:36:48.227 --> 00:36:52.475
I want you to follow the voice of God for yourself.

00:36:52.475 --> 00:36:57.200
Don't go to church somewhere just because I go to church there.

00:37:11.151 --> 00:37:11.462
I want you to go to the church where God has called you to go to church, you know?

00:37:18.360 --> 00:37:22.840
So, I stopped mentioning a lot of places that I'm at all the time because people try to move from all over and they move here.

00:37:22.840 --> 00:37:35.337
One man moved from Florida, was here for a couple weeks, said, You know, Brian, this isn't for me.

00:37:35.337 --> 00:37:37.947
I've got to move back home.

00:37:37.947 --> 00:37:40.160
And I thought, Wow, that was sad.

00:37:40.160 --> 00:37:59.680
He moved over 2,000 miles, was here for a month, sold his house, sold everything to come where we were, and didn't like where we were because it wasn't for him, because he wanted to copycat everything what we're doing and moved back.

00:38:05.455 --> 00:38:22.154
I don't know if he was offended or not or disappointed or whatever, but moved his family back to the Orlando area, and it was amazing because I thought I got to watch really carefully what I say because there's so much influence in this channel that people will just pick up their stuff.

00:38:34.217 --> 00:38:34.451
One man moved from Chicago.

00:38:34.451 --> 00:38:37.698
These people, you just look at them going, Did God tell you to do that?

00:38:37.698 --> 00:38:39.260
Because they act miserable.

00:38:39.260 --> 00:38:42.048
What am I supposed to do now?

00:38:42.048 --> 00:38:50.080
Well, I don't know.

00:38:50.080 --> 00:38:52.347
I'm not your Holy Ghost.

00:38:52.347 --> 00:39:01.936
If he told you to do something, you're going to have instruction and you're going to know what he's told you to do.

00:39:03.853 --> 00:39:08.400
And that's what he went in this book.

00:39:08.400 --> 00:39:12.360
Diana was reading this book and going over things.

00:39:12.360 --> 00:39:22.600
So, just we're picking it like you would pick a chicken off a bone because I want to understand.

00:39:22.600 --> 00:39:25.920
I don't want to live in that.

00:39:27.131 --> 00:39:33.940
And so, with all the stuff that I overcome, y'all, we're all a work in progress.

00:39:34.700 --> 00:40:01.185
And I say it over and over and over again, but it's like when you're dealing with different levels, different devils, and you're dealing with all this stuff, you realize the pattern of offense will keep you out of the will of God.

00:40:18.889 --> 00:40:19.200
It will keep you in that place of lukewarm.

00:40:28.920 --> 00:40:35.320
And because you're always just so touchy, and you go from one place to another offended because of what they said to you, and you go to the next church and you're upset at them, and well, you know, they're just like the other people.

00:40:39.680 --> 00:40:40.328
And he talked about putting people at a standard.

00:40:40.328 --> 00:40:43.949
He goes, well, the world doesn't treat you that way.

00:40:54.840 --> 00:40:55.160
And I say, I used to say that all the time.

00:41:04.640 --> 00:41:05.154
I bet if I hung around Brad Pitt, he wouldn't be that way.

00:41:05.154 --> 00:41:05.840
Just being sarcastic.

00:41:16.360 --> 00:41:16.580
And you keep Why?

00:41:31.891 --> 00:41:32.246
Because what did John say in that book?

00:41:32.246 --> 00:41:37.870
He said it's because the standard that you keep the people.

00:41:37.870 --> 00:41:39.432
It's your expectation of them.

00:41:49.293 --> 00:41:49.698
What are you expecting of the body of Christ?

00:41:50.507 --> 00:41:58.613
You have them at a higher standard of what they should be than what the world would be right here.

00:42:04.650 --> 00:42:04.960
Go ahead.

00:42:20.080 --> 00:42:20.480
I realized that the love I was giving was being sown to the spirit and eventually I would reap those seeds of love.

00:42:27.780 --> 00:42:28.050
I didn't know from where, but I knew the harvest would come.

00:42:28.050 --> 00:42:36.775
No longer did I see it as a failure when love wasn't returned from the person I was giving it to.

00:42:56.320 --> 00:42:56.702
It freed me to love that person even more.

00:42:56.702 --> 00:43:01.600
If more Christians recognize this, they wouldn't give up and become offended.

00:43:01.600 --> 00:43:06.880
Usually, this is not the type of love we walk in.

00:43:06.880 --> 00:43:15.360
We walk in a selfish love that is easily disappointed when our expectations are not met.

00:43:19.933 --> 00:43:20.911
If I have expectations about certain persons, those people can let me down.

00:43:20.911 --> 00:43:27.131
They will disappoint me to the degree that they fall short of my expectations.

00:43:40.960 --> 00:43:41.400
But if I have no expectations about someone, anything given is a blessing and not something owed.

00:43:41.400 --> 00:43:53.220
We set ourselves up for offense when we require certain behaviors from those with whom we have relationships.

00:43:53.220 --> 00:43:58.745
The more we expect, the greater the potential offense.

00:43:58.745 --> 00:43:59.387
Yep.

00:43:59.387 --> 00:44:08.430
The greater the relationship, the greater the expectation, the greater the offense.

00:44:17.303 --> 00:44:17.537
And when you get around leadership, and that's what the Lord told me.

00:44:17.537 --> 00:44:28.033
He said even in this one, I don't want you to be friends with the pastors.

00:44:36.646 --> 00:44:37.011
I want you to honor them as pastors.

00:44:37.011 --> 00:44:39.240
They're not your friends.

00:44:39.240 --> 00:44:40.760
They're your pastors.

00:44:40.760 --> 00:44:56.920
There's so many people say, Well, if I need to go out to dinner with you, I want to know you and I want to hang out with you, let's fist bump and have a donut.

00:44:56.920 --> 00:45:04.270
But the more you get to know them, the more you realize that they're just as human as you are.

00:45:10.000 --> 00:45:12.408
And that's why I even told the people that we go, Hey, listen.

00:45:17.240 --> 00:45:18.305
I don't want to be your friend because you're my pastor.

00:45:21.560 --> 00:45:29.556
I want to separate the friendship from a pastor because the more you become my friend, it's harder for you to be my pastor.

00:45:38.731 --> 00:45:38.909
And you become too familiar with them and then you dishonor them.

00:45:40.547 --> 00:45:41.791
And that's the same thing with my friend Billy Burke.

00:45:41.791 --> 00:45:51.280
If you talk too much to them, you start looking at them as just a normal human being.

00:45:51.280 --> 00:46:01.520
But God put them in your life to be that iron sharpens iron and that mentor.

00:46:01.520 --> 00:46:06.240
There's a line that you don't cross even with joking with people.

00:46:06.240 --> 00:46:14.014
The Lord said always maintain an atmosphere of honor when you're talking to him.

00:46:21.034 --> 00:46:23.090
Do not dishonor him even if you feel well.

00:46:26.680 --> 00:46:29.320
I am just kidding around with you.

00:46:30.860 --> 00:46:45.145
That is why there is a place of honor that I try to keep; not that I am exalting a man of God, but I want to put that pastor in the place of, 'You are my pastor, you are not my friend.

00:46:45.145 --> 00:46:48.000
' Does that make sense?

00:46:48.000 --> 00:47:03.937
There are so many times that I see the congregation—even when I worked for that mega-church in Oklahoma City—always wanting to be the friend of the pastor.

00:47:03.937 --> 00:47:06.560
Let us go to lunch.

00:47:06.560 --> 00:47:10.400
Let us go have a golf game.

00:47:10.400 --> 00:47:13.755
I want to go with you to golf.

00:47:13.755 --> 00:47:17.510
Let us catch a movie or go to the gym and work out.

00:47:17.510 --> 00:47:21.444
They tried to find some kind of ground on how to relate.

00:47:21.444 --> 00:47:38.190
All of a sudden, that pastor they were teaching became no longer able to minister to them because they became too familiar with him and it becomes a toxic relationship very quickly.

00:47:52.156 --> 00:47:52.351
I am going through all the things that I have overcome.

00:47:52.351 --> 00:48:06.113
I have learned to pray and be an armor bearer, and the Lord said, 'Even where we are, sit on the back row and do what I have called you to do.

00:48:06.113 --> 00:48:17.990
It is not for you to have a platform here; it is for you to get refreshed and go dump out more.

00:48:22.900 --> 00:48:25.263
You have a platform; use it and minister to the millions.

00:48:25.263 --> 00:48:35.185
Your job is to get refreshed, drink, and have some substance so that you are refreshed and you walk away going, I can go on another day.

00:48:35.185 --> 00:48:48.080
' Because of the bombardment of growing and doing what God has called us to do, it is very interesting as you try to keep that equilibrium.

00:48:48.080 --> 00:48:51.291
Is that a good way to say it?

00:48:53.810 --> 00:48:54.040
It is an equilibrium.

00:48:54.040 --> 00:49:03.360
There are so many of you I know—because I have the emails and the conversations in public—that say, 'Hey, I am offended.

00:49:04.090 --> 00:49:06.929
I do not go to church anymore.

00:49:06.929 --> 00:49:10.594
' Well, where did the offense come in?

00:49:10.594 --> 00:49:12.480
How did that happen?

00:49:12.480 --> 00:49:14.720
'Well, they said this to me.

00:49:14.720 --> 00:49:17.890
' Did you get too familiar with them?

00:49:17.890 --> 00:49:19.893
Were you a friend to the pastor?

00:49:19.893 --> 00:49:21.817
Did you allow them to correct you?

00:49:21.817 --> 00:49:24.888
Because I am telling you, iron sharpens iron.

00:49:24.888 --> 00:49:26.956
When you see those sparks fly, it happens.

00:49:26.956 --> 00:49:29.156
If you are not being challenged to grow...

00:49:29.156 --> 00:49:35.600
Diana said, 'Brandon, the books that make me grow the most, like these ones, are the ones that I love.

00:49:35.600 --> 00:49:43.095
' They are the ones that challenge you, where you have to think about it for a little bit longer.

00:49:48.848 --> 00:49:49.184
You said, 'I want to throw it out the window when I am driving.

00:49:49.184 --> 00:49:55.880
' Yeah, they make you get mad and you go, 'That is trash, I do not want to do that anymore.

00:49:55.880 --> 00:50:01.740
' But it is sharpening, it is challenging, and it makes you self-examine.

00:50:01.740 --> 00:50:07.869
Judge not lest you be judged; you judge yourself and think, 'Where does this fit me and where am I going wrong?

00:50:07.869 --> 00:50:15.420
' There is somebody who said they read this book four times a year because it keeps them on track from being offended.

00:50:15.680 --> 00:50:19.587
He said he reads it at the first of every quarter.

00:50:22.560 --> 00:50:22.840
I thought, 'That is a wow.

00:50:22.840 --> 00:50:31.400
' But it is how I am with the things the Lord has told me, even with deflecting and giving Him the glory.

00:50:31.400 --> 00:50:34.920
I realize that I am like an airplane that just got off course.

00:50:34.920 --> 00:50:36.360
Just a little bit.

00:50:36.360 --> 00:50:42.520
The more you stay off course, the more you are flying way over here.

00:50:52.453 --> 00:50:52.627
The Lord said, 'Brandon, I told you to do this, this, and this,' and I go, 'Oh, forgive me.

00:50:52.627 --> 00:50:59.818
' He will instruct you about your giving, where He wants you tithing, and where He wants you to stay on course.

00:51:06.273 --> 00:51:06.745
There is so much—if you do not have those refreshers—there are distractions that pull you off.

00:51:09.760 --> 00:51:11.720
It just takes a little bit; just a little nudge gets you off course.

00:51:11.720 --> 00:51:17.940
It is the same thing with offense in your marriage and all kinds of things.

00:51:17.940 --> 00:51:20.973
I try to bring these things to you because it really helps me.

00:51:28.743 --> 00:51:29.011
It is the small foxes that ruin the vines, not the big ones.

00:51:29.011 --> 00:51:33.507
Most people are looking for the major decisions: the divorce, or whatever you are dealing with.

00:51:43.520 --> 00:51:43.903
It did not start with a divorce or adultery; it started with something small.

00:51:43.903 --> 00:51:53.920
It was the small thing that you did not correct while it was small that exploded into something way over here.

00:51:53.920 --> 00:52:03.886
You ask, 'How did we get this far off course?

00:52:03.886 --> 00:52:10.600
' It is because you did not correct it back there.

00:52:31.080 --> 00:52:33.776
Go back to what He instructed you to do before you even got to that place.

00:52:33.776 --> 00:52:55.880
There are the footsteps to keep you on course so that you do not deviate.

00:52:55.880 --> 00:53:03.525
If you do not correct it right there, the whole thing is falling down.

00:53:04.600 --> 00:53:07.273
That is why I am telling you today, let that magnifying glass examine you.

00:53:08.175 --> 00:53:14.608
I feel like I have His gaze; He is observing me.

00:53:16.140 --> 00:53:22.245
There is this need to be fixed immediately.

00:53:38.327 --> 00:53:38.573
I stopped.

00:53:38.573 --> 00:53:40.467
How did I get so fat again?

00:53:41.693 --> 00:53:41.951
I am just being real.

00:53:41.951 --> 00:53:52.470
I weighed today and I was 287 lbs.

00:53:52.480 --> 00:53:54.680
I said, 'Where did I go wrong?

00:53:54.680 --> 00:54:08.720
' It was not the one ice cream; it was the snacking that added up day after day.

00:54:08.720 --> 00:54:18.120
If you do not catch it, the habits end up making you big.

00:54:18.120 --> 00:54:30.833
Habits form patterns.

00:54:53.956 --> 00:54:54.267
It is something so simple and innocent at the time, but it is the little thing that takes you off course.

00:54:54.267 --> 00:55:09.411
When you are way over here, you go, 'Oh Lord, I did not mean to.

00:55:09.411 --> 00:55:19.807
' Stress, financial pressure, life pressure, daughter pressure; you allow that thing to push you and you have unhealthy habits.

00:55:40.320 --> 00:55:40.867
You weigh yourself and you go, 'The clothes that are the biggest are getting tight.

00:55:40.867 --> 00:55:42.045
Correct it.

00:55:42.045 --> 00:55:42.640
' I am here again.

00:55:42.640 --> 00:55:42.910
Same mountain, same thing.

00:55:42.910 --> 00:55:43.650
You go around that mountain all the time.

00:55:43.650 --> 00:55:47.987
You did not learn from the last time.

00:56:04.753 --> 00:56:05.040
I told her before, when I was sacrificing and was exercising so hard, riding five miles a day on my bike.

00:56:05.040 --> 00:56:06.520
I'll never be here again.

00:56:06.520 --> 00:56:08.795
I'll never do this again.

00:56:10.370 --> 00:56:14.377
The next thing you know, one bite at a time, you go over here.

00:56:14.377 --> 00:56:17.057
That's why I challenge myself today.

00:56:17.057 --> 00:56:33.520
By the time my birthday comes, I want to be a certain amount of weight again, but I don't want it to be some place I visit.

00:56:58.360 --> 00:56:58.846
I told her, I said, How do you renew your mind to it that this is not a place you visit?

00:56:58.846 --> 00:57:11.917
That the Holy Spirit says this is a place you must live, for I want you here and I have a job for you to do.

00:57:11.917 --> 00:57:23.133
If you keep going down this road, Jack Coe went home early because of obesity and he had a major call on his life and he was warned.

00:57:23.133 --> 00:57:36.796
Jack Coe went home early; there are other big ministers that went home early that had major calls on their lives that died early because they had addictions to things.

00:57:36.796 --> 00:57:39.720
Some people had alcohol addictions.

00:57:39.720 --> 00:57:44.600
Some people went off in weird left-field theology.

00:57:44.600 --> 00:57:48.780
Some people went off and did certain things.

00:57:48.780 --> 00:57:53.930
You go, I'm not going to throw rocks at glass.

00:57:53.930 --> 00:57:56.815
You know, what do you say?

00:57:56.815 --> 00:58:04.480
Braden says, Well, you have a speck in your own eye and all that.

00:58:04.480 --> 00:58:16.800
We go over that all the time, but I've just tried to be somebody that you all know because I know there's so many people that deal with certain things.

00:58:16.800 --> 00:58:19.600
Does that make sense with y'all tonight?

00:58:26.213 --> 00:58:34.800
I mean, it all started with offense; that is where a lot of it comes back to the root, is offended at stuff, offended at comments, offended at people.

00:58:34.800 --> 00:58:42.020
You try to bury things with food and the bully mentality, coping mechanisms.

00:58:42.020 --> 00:58:52.120
Some people grab alcohol, some people grab marijuana, some people grab maybe some drugs or whatever.

00:59:05.293 --> 00:59:05.467
Some people grab lust and pornography or bad material to read or whatever, but certain people deal with certain things.

00:59:05.467 --> 00:59:07.075
I'm not sitting here justifying anything.

00:59:07.075 --> 00:59:17.720
I'm just trying to say the only one that is going to ever set us free—you'll know the truth and the truth will set you free.

00:59:17.720 --> 00:59:26.484
But when you start to realize, hey, I've got a problem, it's realizing it and confronting it and embracing it and saying, Listen, I'm going to expose this.

00:59:29.370 --> 00:59:29.625
I don't want to live this way no more.

00:59:36.920 --> 00:59:37.080
I don't want to be a statistic.

00:59:39.571 --> 00:59:39.846
I don't know, it's just healthy things.

00:59:39.846 --> 00:59:45.672
Where are we going to be with the body of Christ with this end-time glory, going from glory to glory?

00:59:53.280 --> 00:59:53.525
We all have something.

00:59:53.525 --> 00:59:56.303
We've all got something we're working through.

00:59:56.303 --> 01:00:08.147
But I believe the root of many things starts with offense, or bitterness towards your wife, your husband, your kids, your pastor, your boss, your neighbor, your mom, or your dad.

01:00:08.147 --> 01:00:15.300
You've got something that you didn't get rid of the root of, and you thought, I've got to fix this.

01:00:15.300 --> 01:00:19.255
So Braden told me, I never try to sell you anything.

01:00:19.255 --> 01:00:19.725
Never.

01:00:19.725 --> 01:00:24.200
Never will I ever try to sell you.

01:00:24.200 --> 01:00:30.011
I try very hard to always do exactly what the Holy Spirit has done, and I've done it.

01:00:30.011 --> 01:00:35.058
He showed me this thing about these little emojis.

01:00:35.058 --> 01:00:38.515
YouTube will let us do little emojis on the chat.

01:00:38.515 --> 01:00:45.200
When you all want to talk, you can use custom ones that are a dollar a piece.

01:00:45.200 --> 01:00:49.560
You can charge whatever you want for them.

01:00:56.760 --> 01:00:57.180
I would do it completely for free.

01:00:57.180 --> 01:00:59.044
The minimum is 99 cents.

01:00:59.044 --> 01:01:00.467
That's the lowest you can go.

01:01:03.160 --> 01:01:11.291
I can put these little stickers that you all can use, like, go tubing, the greater glory things that are fun that Braden wanted to design.

01:01:11.509 --> 01:01:15.920
I never want to get you all upset about anything because it's a dollar.

01:01:21.387 --> 01:01:21.613
I would give it away for free, but it's YouTube's thing.

01:01:34.663 --> 01:01:37.973
I think it's fun and I told him, if you want to do it, he's told me, Dad, are the people going to be offended because it's a dollar?

01:01:44.102 --> 01:01:44.307
I said, I don't know, but I'll present it to them because it's him.

01:01:44.307 --> 01:01:54.300
He's wanting to do it and he thinks it's fun to make these little emojis because he watches the chat with you all.

01:01:54.300 --> 01:02:02.086
He's like, Do you think the people will get ticked off because it's a buck?

01:02:09.120 --> 01:02:11.560
He goes, Dad, I'd charge them a quarter, but it won't allow me to.

01:02:11.560 --> 01:02:23.053
I'm not presenting this to you asking for permission; I'm just going to tell you it's going to be there and if you want to buy it, it's for YouTube.

01:02:32.933 --> 01:02:33.338
He thought it would be fun to play around with.

01:02:33.338 --> 01:02:37.120
If you think it'd be fun, you can do it.

01:02:37.120 --> 01:02:40.240
If not, there's nothing there.

01:02:40.240 --> 01:02:42.138
It's for every 30 days.

